    "Beijing The study aims to evaluate STEM Teachers' Preparation, Teaching Beliefs, and Perceived Teaching Competence.",
    "The study indicates that better training and teaching practice, combined with positive beliefs about teaching, enhance STEM teachers' confidence in their teaching abilities, with these beliefs acting as a bridge between practice and perceived competence.",
    "Quantitative 219 N/I Zhan et al.",
    "2021 Shanghai The study aimed to explore junior secondary school teachers' perceptions of IEIS and investigate the factors that affect IEIS in STEM education The research indicated that while science teachers have a solid grasp of engineering concepts and education, they struggle to differentiate between engineering and scientific practices, often integrate these subjects at a basic level, and face a shortage of advanced training programs in STEM education Mixed method 1185 N/I Dan and Gary, 2018 Hong Kong The study aims to understand teachers' expectations toward PD and develop a conceptual PD model for integrated STEM.",
    "The study concluded that Teachers face internal professional development challenges, struggle with applying learned knowledge, address diverse needs and skills, and align with their values."
